comment_data.body:
This problem is not limited to the case of `nvim_get_proc`. Occurs on all calls that handle events internally.

Ex.
```
nvim -u NORC --cmd 'call system("pwd")' --cmd 'se gcr='
nvim -u NORC --cmd 'sleep 500m' --cmd 'set gcr='
```

It seems to be fixed by changing the `ui_call_mode_info_set` call to be delayed if `starting` is `true`, as in the following patch. However, this change may cause some new problems.

```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/ui.c b/src/nvim/ui.c
index 45959b7b6..8ab3c5513 100644
--- a/src/nvim/ui.c
+++ b/src/nvim/ui.c
@@ -501,7 +501,7 @@ void ui_flush(void)
     ui_call_grid_cursor_goto(cursor_grid_handle, cursor_row, cursor_col);
     pending_cursor_update = false;
   }
-  if (pending_mode_info_update) {
+  if (pending_mode_info_update && !starting) {
     Arena arena = ARENA_EMPTY;
     Array style = mode_style_array(&arena);
     bool enabled = (*p_guicursor != NUL);
```

Related #18932
